<dl id="n09017l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09017l">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09017l"> 17(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Columbus / Newton / Einstein ( Sign in heavens</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">It is perhaps interesting to speculate on the practical consequences of <mark>Einstein&apos;s discovery</mark>. I do not doubt that he will be believed. A prophet who can give <mark>signs in the heavens</mark> is always believed. No one ever seriously questioned <mark>Newton&apos;s theory</mark> after the return of Halley&apos;s comet. <small> J. B. S. Haldane, <a name="DAED" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#DAED"><cite title="source">Dedalus</cite></a> (1923) 13f</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
